cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper focuses on contextualized word embeddings derived from pre-trained language models and their performance on downstream NLP tasks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses pre-trained language models as fixed feature extractors and compares their performance on downstream tasks, which involves machine learning techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper deals with natural language processing and uses pre-trained language models to improve performance on NLP tasks, which falls under the umbrella of AI. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper uses nearest neighbor analysis to evaluate the embeddings, which is a common technique in information retrieval. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses neural network-based language models to generate embeddings and evaluate their performance, which falls under the scope of neural computing.
